al purchaser. This is much better than simply repairing the old mattress as the mattress will be replaced with the same model (as long as that model remains in production). Emma will arrange for the pick up of the damaged mattress and have the new mattress shipped to your doorstep, all complementary to the original purchaser.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jgrJph iGtnpe pf-147_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-148_"><h4 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bSqaIl iXTDAP pf-149_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-151_">How does the return-and-replacement process work?&nbsp;</span></h4><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-gHjyzD dQAIat pf-152_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-itWPBs dKPonY pf-153_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-155_">If your mattress is eligible for replacement* and if you wish to return your mattress, you may reach out to Customer Care at support@emma-sleep.ca or 1-888-585-EMMA. For an easier application, you can have your order number ready along with photos of the damage.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-itWPBs dKPonY pf-156_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-158_">Emma holds the right to ask for proof of damage along with the application of warranty. This proof can include, though is not limited to photos of the damage in such a way that there is little to no reasonable doubt of the extent of the damage. The warranty shall not apply if Emma determines that the damage is the result of misuse or neglect. It is at Emma’s discretion to determine if the damage such as but not limited to odors, burns, cuts, infestation, or bodily fluids was reasonably the result of normal use and/or production faults.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-itWPBs dKPonY pf-159_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-161_">If the warranty application is approved, Emma will arrange for your mattress to be picked up from your house and replaced, free of charge. The product will be replaced with the same model (as long as that model remains in production), and no upgrades will be made/offered. Shipping costs of the new Emma mattress as placement will be the responsibility of Emma. (Please note that shipping to a new address, different from the original purchase, may incur additional fees.) </span></li></ul><p class="sc-ehIJor eZpnKY pf-162_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-164_">*The 10-year Warranty only covers the replacement of defective or damaged mattress. Refunds can only be applied within the 365-Night Trial Period exclusively offered to Emma customers so they can try out and enjoy the benefits of their Emma mattress within reasonable time before making a decision.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jgrJph iGtnpe pf-165_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gXRojI kCnmwO pf-166_"><h4 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-bSqaIl iXTDAP pf-167_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-169_">Disclaimer, Limitation on Liability</span></h4><p class="sc-ehIJor eZpnKY pf-170_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-BHvUt fJlZte pf-172_">TO THE EXTENT PERMISSIBLE BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE EMMA ORIGINAL IS PROVIDED “AS IS” AND THIS WARRANTY AND ANY IMPLIED WARRANTIES ARE YOUR EXCLUSIVE WARRANTIES AND REPLACE ALL OTHER WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. SOME PROVINCES OR TERRITORIES DO NOT ALLOW LIMITATIONS ON HOW LONG AN IMPLIED WARRANTY LASTS, SO THE ABOVE LIMITATION MAY NOT APPLY TO YOU.
